page.title: 09EMPLOYMENT: DANE END & AREA
page.content: There is very little employment in the D-Block. Those who work in the immediate vicinity are either self employed, work on a farm or work at the hotel just outside the block. There are also several game keepers and a grave-digger. {LIST OF OCCUPATIONS:}barman, bricklayer, buyer, caretaker, carpenter, cleaner, computer analyst/programmer, draughtsman, electrician,estate agent, foreman-factory/building trade, game keeper, glass worker, grave digger, hotel worker, insurance broker, jeweller. lorry driver, mechanic, metal polisher, plumber, printer, quantity surveyor, road builder, salesman,scientist, solicitor, teacher, thatcher. People{travel mainly by private car to the towns around us but some go to{London.
